@startuml recall-consolidate-query-union
' Query union sequence: resolve the latest shard + its consolidated_lsn
' watermark -> search Recall (lsn > watermark, brute-force exact) and the
' Consolidate shard (FAISS via the SSD/RAM cache) -> merge: square pgvector
' L2 -> L2^2 (metric alignment), recall-wins dedup, suppress recall-tombstoned
' ids, sort ascending, take top_k. Also shows the no-shard recall/ephemeral
' branch and the mode label (which always reflects the consolidated-shard cache only).

title Query union: search Recall + Consolidate, then merge (RB_RECALL on)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "client" as client
participant "query_dp\n(run_query)" as dp
database "shard_catalog\n(consolidated_lsn)" as catalog
participant "_search_consolidated_shard\n(FAISS via SSD/RAM cache)" as consolidated
database "Recall\n(pgvector, recall_search)" as recall

client -> dp : POST /query {vector, top_k, filter}
activate dp

== Resolve the seam ONCE (_resolve_shard): the watermark of the shard this query will read ==

dp -> catalog : _resolve_shard -> list_shards -> latest shard S\n(cheap catalog lookup; yields consolidated_lsn = W)
alt no shard yet (list_shards empty)
  note right of dp #E9F7E9
    Watermark W = 0 -> every Recall row qualifies.
    Answer SYNCHRONOUSLY from Recall (read-your-writes
    for a brand-new dataset). Does NOT fall to ephemeral.
  end note
end

== Overlap (#31): consolidated FAISS search and Recall scan run CONCURRENTLY (recall needs only W) ==

note over dp
  After ONE resolution, run both INDEPENDENT searches concurrently:
  recall scan on a bounded worker thread (request OTel context re-attached
  so recall.search stays a child of the request span), FAISS search inline.
  Union wall-time ~ max(consolidated, recall), not the sum (~15 ms tax erased).
end note

par consolidated FAISS search (inline)
  dp -> consolidated : _search_consolidated_shard(S)\n(FAISS, L2^2) via SSD/RAM cache
  activate consolidated
  consolidated --> dp : consolidated hits (L2^2)
  deactivate consolidated
else Recall scan (worker thread)
  dp -> recall : recall_search WHERE tenant, dataset,\nlsn > W (the watermark of the shard this query READ,\nNOT a fresh list_shards), filter
  activate recall
  note right of recall
    Brute-force exact L2 over the SMALL recall partition.
    Score computed as power(embedding <-> q, 2) = L2^2,
    so it merges DIRECTLY with the consolidated shard's FAISS L2^2.
    Returns BOTH live matches and the FULL set of recall ids
    above W (incl. tombstoned / filtered-out / past-top_k).
  end note
  recall --> dp : recall hits (L2^2) + full recall-id set above W
  deactivate recall
end

note over dp #FBE9E9
  Error precedence on a double failure: consolidated error wins (preserves
  the pre-overlap serial ordering). A recall failure is never masked; a
  consolidated failure is never reported as a recall error.
end note

== Merge ==

dp -> dp : (1) METRIC ALIGNMENT -- square pgvector L2 -> L2^2\n(over identical un-normalised vectors; the most likely silent bug)
dp -> dp : (2) DEDUP recall-wins -- any consolidated hit whose id is in the\nfull recall-id-set-above-W is dropped (Recall is newer)
dp -> dp : (3) SUPPRESS tombstones -- a deleted/filtered recall row\nsuppresses its consolidated twin but contributes NO match\n(only a filter-passing LIVE recall row adds a match)
dp -> dp : (4) SORT ascending by L2^2, take top_k

== mode label (reflects the consolidated-shard cache only, never Recall) ==

note over dp #FDF3E7
  consolidated resolved (warm) -> mode=hot   | consolidated resolved (load) -> mode=cold
  no consolidated shard, recall answered -> mode=recall
  no consolidated shard, no recall row    -> mode=ephemeral (+ job_id)
  So hot/cold does NOT imply Recall was idle -- the label
  only describes the consolidated-shard cache state.
end note

dp --> client : {matches, mode, ...}
deactivate dp

@enduml
